File: plugins/slack/src/tools/create-channel.ts, lines 40-48.

The current code calls slackApi('conversations.setTopic', { channel: data.channel.id, topic: params.topic }) without checking if data.channel.id is defined. The type annotation declares id as optional (id?: string). If id is undefined, slackApi's parameter serialization (slack-api.ts lines 371-375) silently skips the undefined value, sending a setTopic request with no channel parameter. Slack returns an error, caught by the try-catch, producing a misleading warning about 'failed to set topic' when the real issue is a missing channel ID.

Fix: Add a guard before the setTopic call:
```typescript
if (params.topic) {
  if (!data.channel.id) {
    warning = 'Channel created but could not set topic: missing channel ID in API response';
  } else {
    try {
      await slackApi('conversations.setTopic', { channel: data.channel.id, topic: params.topic });
    } catch (err) {
      warning = `Channel created but failed to set topic: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`;
    }
  }
}
```
